### 4.6 `StepperSeparator`

This is the divider between steps. Its rendering differs by orientation:

- Horizontal: a thin horizontal line (`h-px flex-1`) positioned in the items row, between the trigger circles. It needs to visually sit at the vertical midpoint of the trigger circle (center-aligned with the circle).
- Vertical: a thin vertical line running down the left side, below the trigger of the upper step.

For the horizontal case the separator lives between `StepperItem` siblings. The orientation is read from root context.

```tsx
function StepperSeparator({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"div">) {
  const { orientation } = useStepper()

  return (
    <div
      data-slot="stepper-separator"
      data-orientation={orientation}
      className={cn(
        "bg-border transition-colors",
        orientation === "horizontal"
          ? "mt-4 h-px flex-1 self-auto"
          : "ms-4 w-px self-stretch",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}
```

Design notes:
- Horizontal: `mt-4` pushes it down to align with the vertical center of a `size-8` trigger (trigger is 2rem = 32px; `mt-4` = 16px is half, centering the line at the trigger's center).
- Horizontal: `flex-1 self-auto` makes the line expand to fill the gap between items.
- Vertical: `ms-4` aligns the line with the horizontal center of the `size-8` trigger (trigger is `size-8`, so `ms-4` = 16px = half of 32px — centering the line under the trigger).
- Vertical: `w-px self-stretch` makes the line extend the full height of its flex container.
- `transition-colors` allows potential future color-change on completion.

### 4.7 `StepperContent`

Supports two usage patterns: inside `StepperItem` (reads value from item context) or standalone inside `Stepper` (accepts own `value` prop).

```tsx
function StepperContent({
  value: valueProp,
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & { value?: string }) {
  const { value: activeValue } = useStepper()
  const itemContext = useStepperItem()

  // Resolve the value: prefer item context, fall back to prop
  const resolvedValue = itemContext?.value ?? valueProp

  if (resolvedValue === undefined) {
    throw new Error(
      "StepperContent requires a value prop when used outside of a <StepperItem />"
    )
  }

  if (activeValue !== resolvedValue) {
    return null
  }

  return (
    <div
      data-slot="stepper-content"
      className={cn("mt-2", className)}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  )
}
```

Design notes:
- The component returns `null` when not active — this is a simple hide/show approach consistent with the zero-dependency requirement (no Radix AnimatePresence).
- The throw for missing value only fires in development. Production builds could simply return null silently, but the throw aids developer experience.
- `mt-2` provides spacing between the stepper header row and content in horizontal mode. For vertical mode, content rendered inside `StepperItem` naturally follows the title/description.

