# Stepper Compound Component — Implementation Plan

## Context

The shadcn/ui component library has no stepper/wizard component. This adds a `Stepper` compound component for multi-step wizards and onboarding flows, following the exact patterns of existing components (`carousel.tsx` for context, `tabs.tsx` for orientation). No Radix UI primitive exists for a stepper, so the component manages its own state via `React.createContext`.

The task requires **only new files** plus registry entry insertions (registry config files, not component files).

---

## Files to Create

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx` | Compound component |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx` | Demo example |

## Files to Modify (registry config only, not components)

| File | Change |
|------|--------|
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts` | Insert entry after line 563 (between `spinner` and `switch`) |
| `apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` | Insert entry after line 2124 (between `spinner-item` and `switch-demo`) |

---

## Architecture

### Dual-Context Pattern (mirrors `form.tsx` + `carousel.tsx`)

```
StepperContext       — root: { value, onValueChange, orientation }
StepperItemContext   — per-item: { value, disabled, completed }
```

- `StepperContext` defaults to `null`; `useStepper()` throws if used outside `<Stepper>` (same as `useCarousel()`)
- `StepperItemContext` defaults to `null`; `useStepperItem()` returns `null` silently (so `StepperContent` can be used standalone)

### Controlled + Uncontrolled State

```tsx
const [internalValue, setInternalValue] = React.useState<string>(defaultValue)
const isControlled = controlledValue !== undefined
const value = isControlled ? controlledValue : internalValue
// onValueChange fires in both modes
```

### Orientation via `data-orientation` + Tailwind group selectors (mirrors `tabs.tsx`)

- `data-orientation="horizontal|vertical"` on root `<div>`
- `group/stepper` class names the group for child targeting
- `group/stepper-item` named on each item for child text-alignment selectors

---

## Sub-components (all in `stepper.tsx`)

### 1. `Stepper` — Root container
- Props: `value?`, `defaultValue?`, `onValueChange?`, `orientation?` (`"horizontal"` default)
- Provides `StepperContext`
- `data-slot="stepper"`, `data-orientation`
- Classes: `group/stepper flex flex-col gap-4`

### 2. `StepperItem` — Per-step wrapper
- Props: `value` (required), `disabled?`, `completed?`
- Provides `StepperItemContext`
- `data-slot="stepper-item"`, `data-state="active|inactive"`, `data-completed=""`, `data-disabled=""`
- Horizontal classes: `flex-1 flex-col items-center gap-2`
- Vertical classes: `flex-row items-start gap-3`

### 3. `StepperTrigger` — Clickable step indicator
- Props: standard `<button>` props
- Reads from both contexts; throws if used outside `<StepperItem>`
- Calls `onValueChange(value)` on click; respects `disabled`
- `data-slot="stepper-trigger"`, `data-state`, `data-completed`, `data-disabled`
- Default classes: `size-8 rounded-full border-2` circle with:
  - inactive: `border-muted-foreground/30 text-muted-foreground`
  - `data-[state=active]:border-primary data-[state=active]:bg-primary data-[state=active]:text-primary-foreground`
  - `data-[completed]:border-primary data-[completed]:bg-primary data-[completed]:text-primary-foreground`
  - `focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2`

### 4. `StepperTitle` — Step title
- `<p>` element, `data-slot="stepper-title"`
- `text-sm font-medium leading-none`
- `group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:text-center`

### 5. `StepperDescription` — Step description
- `<p>` element, `data-slot="stepper-description"`
- `text-xs text-muted-foreground`
- `group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:text-center`

### 6. `StepperSeparator` — Visual connector between steps
- `<div>`, reads `orientation` from root context
- `data-slot="stepper-separator"`, `data-orientation`
- Horizontal: `h-px flex-1 self-auto bg-border` (expands between items, aligns via `items-center` on wrapping div)
- Vertical: `ms-4 w-px self-stretch bg-border` (`ms-4` = 16px centers line under `size-8` trigger)

### 7. `StepperContent` — Content panel (active step only)
- Props: `value?` (for standalone use outside `<StepperItem>`)
- Dual usage: reads from `StepperItemContext` when nested inside `<StepperItem>`, falls back to own `value` prop when standalone
- Returns `null` when the resolved value ≠ active step
- Throws if neither item context nor `value` prop is available
- `data-slot="stepper-content"`, `mt-2`

---

## `stepper.tsx` — Full Implementation

```tsx
"use client"

import * as React from "react"

import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// ─── Types ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

type StepperOrientation = "horizontal" | "vertical"

type StepperProps = {
  value?: string
  defaultValue?: string
  onValueChange?: (value: string) => void
  orientation?: StepperOrientation
}

type StepperContextValue = {
  value: string
  onValueChange: (value: string) => void
  orientation: StepperOrientation
}

type StepperItemContextValue = {
  value: string
  disabled: boolean
  completed: boolean
}

// ─── Root Context ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

const StepperContext = React.createContext<StepperContextValue | null>(null)

function useStepper(): StepperContextValue {
  const context = React.useContext(StepperContext)
  if (!context) {
    throw new Error("useStepper must be used within a <Stepper />")
  }
  return context
}

// ─── Item Context ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

const StepperItemContext =
  React.createContext<StepperItemContextValue | null>(null)

function useStepperItem(): StepperItemContextValue | null {
  return React.useContext(StepperItemContext)
}

// ─── Components ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

function Stepper({
  value: controlledValue,
  defaultValue = "",
  onValueChange,
  orientation = "horizontal",
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & StepperProps) {
  const [internalValue, setInternalValue] = React.useState<string>(defaultValue)

  const isControlled = controlledValue !== undefined
  const value = isControlled ? controlledValue : internalValue

  const handleValueChange = React.useCallback(
    (newValue: string) => {
      if (!isControlled) {
        setInternalValue(newValue)
      }
      onValueChange?.(newValue)
    },
    [isControlled, onValueChange]
  )

  return (
    <StepperContext.Provider
      value={{ value, onValueChange: handleValueChange, orientation }}
    >
      <div
        data-slot="stepper"
        data-orientation={orientation}
        className={cn("group/stepper flex flex-col gap-4", className)}
        {...props}
      >
        {children}
      </div>
    </StepperContext.Provider>
  )
}

function StepperItem({
  value,
  disabled = false,
  completed = false,
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & {
  value: string
  disabled?: boolean
  completed?: boolean
}) {
  const { value: activeValue, orientation } = useStepper()
  const isActive = activeValue === value

  return (
    <StepperItemContext.Provider value={{ value, disabled, completed }}>
      <div
        data-slot="stepper-item"
        data-state={isActive ? "active" : "inactive"}
        {...(completed ? { "data-completed": "" } : {})}
        {...(disabled ? { "data-disabled": "" } : {})}
        data-orientation={orientation}
        className={cn(
          "group/stepper-item flex",
          orientation === "horizontal"
            ? "flex-1 flex-col items-center gap-2"
            : "flex-row items-start gap-3",
          className
        )}
        {...props}
      >
        {children}
      </div>
    </StepperItemContext.Provider>
  )
}

function StepperTrigger({
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"button">) {
  const { value: activeValue, onValueChange } = useStepper()
  const itemContext = useStepperItem()

  if (!itemContext) {
    throw new Error("StepperTrigger must be used within a <StepperItem />")
  }

  const { value, disabled, completed } = itemContext
  const isActive = activeValue === value

  return (
    <button
      type="button"
      data-slot="stepper-trigger"
      data-state={isActive ? "active" : "inactive"}
      {...(completed ? { "data-completed": "" } : {})}
      {...(disabled ? { "data-disabled": "" } : {})}
      disabled={disabled}
      onClick={() => {
        if (!disabled) {
          onValueChange(value)
        }
      }}
      className={cn(
        "inline-flex size-8 shrink-0 cursor-pointer items-center justify-center rounded-full border-2 text-sm font-medium transition-colors",
        "border-muted-foreground/30 text-muted-foreground",
        "data-[state=active]:border-primary data-[state=active]:bg-primary data-[state=active]:text-primary-foreground",
        "data-[completed]:border-primary data-[completed]:bg-primary data-[completed]:text-primary-foreground",
        "disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:opacity-50",
        "focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </button>
  )
}

function StepperTitle({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"p">) {
  return (
    <p
      data-slot="stepper-title"
      className={cn(
        "text-sm font-medium leading-none",
        "group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:text-center",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}

function StepperDescription({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"p">) {
  return (
    <p
      data-slot="stepper-description"
      className={cn(
        "text-xs text-muted-foreground",
        "group-data-[orientation=horizontal]/stepper-item:text-center",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}

function StepperSeparator({ className, ...props }: React.ComponentProps<"div">) {
  const { orientation } = useStepper()

  return (
    <div
      data-slot="stepper-separator"
      data-orientation={orientation}
      className={cn(
        "bg-border transition-colors",
        orientation === "horizontal"
          ? "mt-4 h-px flex-1 self-auto"
          : "ms-4 w-px self-stretch",
        className
      )}
      {...props}
    />
  )
}

function StepperContent({
  value: valueProp,
  className,
  children,
  ...props
}: React.ComponentProps<"div"> & { value?: string }) {
  const { value: activeValue } = useStepper()
  const itemContext = useStepperItem()

  const resolvedValue = itemContext?.value ?? valueProp

  if (resolvedValue === undefined) {
    throw new Error(
      "StepperContent requires a value prop when used outside of a <StepperItem />"
    )
  }

  if (activeValue !== resolvedValue) {
    return null
  }

  return (
    <div
      data-slot="stepper-content"
      className={cn("mt-2", className)}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </div>
  )
}

// ─── Exports ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

export {
  Stepper,
  StepperItem,
  StepperTrigger,
  StepperTitle,
  StepperDescription,
  StepperSeparator,
  StepperContent,
}
```

---

## `stepper-demo.tsx` — Full Implementation

