## Key Design Decisions

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| No Radix UI dependency | No Radix primitive for steppers exists; React context is sufficient |
| Dual context (`StepperContext` + `StepperItemContext`) | Root context for orientation/active-step; item context for per-step value/state — mirrors `form.tsx` |
| `StepperContent` accepts optional `value` prop | Enables standalone use (horizontal demo) without requiring nesting inside `StepperItem` |
| `data-[completed]:` separate from `data-[state=active]:` | Completed and active are independent states (a completed step can be revisited/active again) |
| `StepperSeparator` reads orientation from context | Renders `h-px flex-1` (horizontal) vs `ms-4 w-px self-stretch` (vertical) automatically |
| `ms-4` on vertical separator | Aligns the 1px line under the center of the `size-8` (32px) trigger circle (16px = half of 32px) |

